![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

This panel enables the generation of spool commands to select the input tray (and thus the type of paper) for the printer.

> Note

Tray commands are used only when using PCL or PostScript spool types.

When the feature is enabled, the tray can be selected from a static list or read from a user attribute. The list is processed from top to bottom and the attribute is evaluated. The first rule that is verified determines which tray to use. If no rule is verified, a default value is used.

**Option**

**Description**

**Enable the input tray selection for PostScript or PCL**

Enable the tray selection rules.

**Static**

The tray number is selected from the list of preconfigured trays.

**Dynamic**

The tray number is read from a user attribute.

**Default Tray**

The number of the tray to be used if no tray rule is resolved.

**Tray Mapping**

A list of user-configured trays and their associated boolean user attribute.

## **Managing tray mapping**
**![](data:image/png;base64,)**

### Adding a tray mapping
Click the ![](data:image/png;base64,) button to create a new tray mapping.

- Each mapping contains the tray number and a user-defined boolean attribute to enable the use of the tray.

### Editing a tray mapping
- Double click on the cell corresponding to the tray number to edit it.

- Drag a boolean attribute in the **Attribute **cell.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

### Deleting a tray mapping
- Select the tray mapping that you wish to delete.

- Click the button &nbsp;![](data:image/png;base64,) .
